 The Non-Academic Staff Union of Universities, NASU is set for a nationwide protest over the ongoing National strike action embarked upon by the Joint Action committee. According to a document obtained by The Nation the protest tagged “Peaceful rally” will hold on March 8 in University of Abuja. The non-academic staff union members are protesting against alleged disparity in payment of Earned allowance to workers in Nigerian Universities. It should be recalled that the workers went on strike on December 4,2017 but after a meeting with the Federal Government on December 19, nothing has been heard on negotiations with leadership of JAC claiming that it is yet to hear from the Federal government.